SIMPLE: saucy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saucy
<hw>Sau"cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Saucier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Sauciest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[From <er>Sauce</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Showing impertinent boldness or pertness; transgressing
the rules of decorum; treating superiors with contempt; impudent;
insolent; <as>as, a <ex>saucy</ex> fellow</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Am I not protector, <qex>saucy</qex> priest?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Expressive of, or characterized by, impudence;
impertinent; <as>as, a <ex>saucy</ex> eye; <ex>saucy</ex>
looks</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We then have done you bold and <qex>saucy</qex> wrongs.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Impudent; insolent; impertinent; rude.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sauerkraut</ent>⟦br⟧
